text: Only stall selling brown rice at this area. 4.90 today. Very salty especially for any dish with gravy. and oily too.
Food is pretty average here. Cai Fan has long queue, dishes are tasty but a little oily, good pricing compared to other stalls. Fish soup and braised pork rice were not too bad.

Economic vegetable rice is very good. Queue however can be pretty long and it is usually quite a long wait before getting served.
Store with herbal soup is also quite popular.

There are Japanese cuisine, lor mee, mix rice, spinach soup noodles, curry rice etc. Total 5 food stores. Can try. All not great but not bad also.

The drinks store however, their coffee tea Milo, all cannot make it. If you must, only order can drinks.
Mix veg rice quite good. Good value. Very long queue if you arrive at around 12 noon, good luck.
